      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-core): use local.modelPath for status identity so local indexes stay clean after rebuild",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem**: After rebuilding a local embedding index with a custom memorySearch.local.modelPath, memory status reports Dirty: yes because the status identity resolution uses settings.model (empty string for local provider) while indexing writes local.modelPath as the provider model identity.\n- **Fix**: Add resolveConfiguredLocalModel() that returns local.modelPath for local providers. The identity chain in resolveCurrentIndexIdentityState now checks it before falling through to settings.model.\n- **Root cause**: manager-sync-ops.ts:314 — configuredProvider.model only looked at this.settings.model, ignoring this.settings.local?.modelPath.\n\nCloses #91001\n\n## Changed files\n\n- extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-sync-ops.ts: +2/-1 identity resolution\n- extensions/memory-core/src/memory/embeddings.ts: +13 new helper\n- extensions/memory-core/src/memory/embeddings.test.ts: +33 4 new tests\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Environment: Windows 11, Node 22.22.3\n- All 8 runtime proof assertions pass (local with modelPath, local without, non-local, whitespace, absent config, identity chain)\n- What was not tested: Full Docker/GGUF rebuild flow (needs real .gguf file). Fix is narrow source-level: adds one property to the identity chain, which was already tested by existing identity tests.\n\n## Security Impact\n\nAll 5 questions: No.\n\n## Risks\n\nMinimal blast radius: helper only returns for provider=local with non-empty modelPath. All other providers unaffected. Uses || fallthrough, so when helper returns undefined behavior is identical to before.\n",
